The firewall is a suggestion, not a rule.
Knowledge speaks, but wisdom listens.
The packet never lies, only the analyzer deceives.
In the theater of security, every actor is suspect.
A closed door is just an unlocked question.
The map is not the territory, but it shows the way.
Curiosity is the engine of progress.
To hack is to understand. To understand is to question.
The system reveals itself to those who knock.
Silence speaks louder than firewalls.